# Figma-to-Code Workflow with shadcn/ui

## Overview

This project uses a structured workflow for converting Figma designs to code:
- **Layout & Spacing**: Replicated exactly from Figma using Tailwind utilities
- **UI Components**: Built with shadcn/ui components (never raw HTML primitives)
- **Custom Styles**: Tailwind classes only (no bespoke CSS unless explicitly required)

---

## Pre-Flight: Component Mapping (MANDATORY)

Before generating ANY code from a Figma design, you MUST:

1. **Analyze the design** and list all UI elements
2. **Map each element** to shadcn components or Tailwind primitives
3. **Present the mapping table** for user confirmation
4. **Wait for approval** before writing code

### Mapping Table Format

```
| Figma Element | shadcn Component | Props/Variants |
|---------------|------------------|----------------|
| Primary CTA | Button | variant="default" size="lg" |
| Secondary action | Button | variant="secondary" |
| Form field | Input | type="text" |
| Card container | Card, CardHeader, CardContent | - |
| Modal | Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader | - |
```

### Example Pre-Flight Response

"Before I implement this design, here's my component mapping:

| Figma Element | Implementation |
|---------------|----------------|
| Hero CTA | `Button` variant="default" size="lg" className="rounded-full" |
| Nav links | `Button` variant="ghost" |
| Search field | `Input` with search icon |
| User menu | `DropdownMenu` + `Avatar` |
| Settings modal | `Dialog` + `DialogContent` |

Please confirm this mapping, or let me know any changes before I proceed."

---

## shadcn Component Requirements

### MUST Use shadcn Components For:

| UI Element | shadcn Component(s) |
|------------|---------------------|
| Buttons | `Button` |
| Text inputs | `Input` |
| Textareas | `Textarea` |
| Checkboxes | `Checkbox` |
| Radio buttons | `RadioGroup`, `RadioGroupItem` |
| Toggle switches | `Switch` |
| Dropdowns/Selects | `Select`, `SelectTrigger`, `SelectContent`, `SelectItem` |
| Modals/Dialogs | `Dialog`, `DialogTrigger`, `DialogContent`, `DialogHeader`, `DialogFooter` |
| Confirmation modals | `AlertDialog` + sub-components |
| Popovers | `Popover`, `PopoverTrigger`, `PopoverContent` |
| Tooltips | `Tooltip`, `TooltipTrigger`, `TooltipContent` |
| Tabs | `Tabs`, `TabsList`, `TabsTrigger`, `TabsContent` |
| Cards | `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter` |
| Tables | `Table`, `TableHeader`, `TableBody`, `TableRow`, `TableHead`, `TableCell` |
| Alerts/Banners | `Alert`, `AlertTitle`, `AlertDescription` |
| Badges/Tags | `Badge` |
| Avatars | `Avatar`, `AvatarImage`, `AvatarFallback` |
| Dividers | `Separator` |
| Loading states | `Skeleton` |
| Slide-out panels | `Sheet`, `SheetTrigger`, `SheetContent` |
| Context menus | `ContextMenu` + sub-components |
| Dropdown menus | `DropdownMenu`, `DropdownMenuTrigger`, `DropdownMenuContent`, `DropdownMenuItem` |
| Navigation menus | `NavigationMenu` + sub-components |
| Command palettes | `Command` + sub-components |
| Date pickers | `Calendar`, `Popover` |
| Toasts | `Sonner` (toast function) |
| Progress bars | `Progress` |
| Sliders | `Slider` |
| Accordions | `Accordion`, `AccordionItem`, `AccordionTrigger`, `AccordionContent` |
| Collapsibles | `Collapsible`, `CollapsibleTrigger`, `CollapsibleContent` |
| Scroll areas | `ScrollArea` |
| Form labels | `Label` |

### FORBIDDEN Patterns

Never implement these when shadcn equivalents exist:

```tsx
// ❌ FORBIDDEN
<button className="...">Click me</button>
<input type="text" className="..." />
<select><option>...</option></select>
<dialog>...</dialog>
<div role="checkbox">...</div>

// ✅ REQUIRED
<Button>Click me</Button>
<Input type="text" />
<Select>...</Select>
<Dialog>...</Dialog>
<Checkbox />
```

### Component Availability Check

Before using a component:

1. Check if it exists in `@/components/ui/`
2. If missing, use shadcn MCP `list_components` to verify availability
3. If available in shadcn, install: `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`
4. If not in shadcn, compose from existing shadcn primitives + Tailwind

### Import Pattern

Always import from the local ui directory:

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input"
import { Card, CardHeader, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"
```

---

## Styling Rules

### Priority Order

1. **shadcn variant/prop** - Use built-in variants first
   ```tsx
   <Button variant="outline" size="lg">
   ```

2. **Tailwind className override** - For design-specific adjustments
   ```tsx
   <Button className="rounded-full bg-black">
   ```

3. **Arbitrary Tailwind values** - For exact Figma measurements
   ```tsx
   <div className="w-[347px] gap-[18px]">
   ```

4. **Custom CSS** - Last resort, must justify why Tailwind can't achieve it

### Layout from Figma

Use Tailwind utilities to match Figma exactly:

- **Spacing**: `p-4`, `gap-6`, `m-[18px]` (arbitrary for exact values)
- **Sizing**: `w-full`, `h-[56px]`, `max-w-[600px]`
- **Flexbox**: `flex`, `items-center`, `justify-between`
- **Grid**: `grid`, `grid-cols-3`, `gap-4`
- **Position**: `relative`, `absolute`, `fixed`, `inset-0`
- **Breakpoints**: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`

### UI Chrome from shadcn

Use component props for styling, override with className only when necessary:

```tsx
// Prefer variants
<Button variant="secondary">  // Not className="bg-gray-100"
<Badge variant="outline">     // Not className="border border-gray-200"
<Alert variant="destructive"> // Not className="bg-red-100 text-red-800"

// Override only for design-specific needs
<Button variant="default" className="rounded-full h-12">
```

---

## Figma Layer Name Recognition

When you see these layer names in Figma, map to shadcn:

### Buttons
- `Button`, `Button/Default`, `PrimaryButton` → `Button variant="default"`
- `Button/Secondary`, `SecondaryButton` → `Button variant="secondary"`
- `Button/Outline`, `OutlineButton` → `Button variant="outline"`
- `Button/Ghost`, `GhostButton` → `Button variant="ghost"`
- `Button/Destructive`, `DestructiveButton` → `Button variant="destructive"`
- `Button/Link`, `LinkButton` → `Button variant="link"`
- `Button/Icon`, `IconButton` → `Button size="icon"`
- `Button/SM`, `SmallButton` → `Button size="sm"`
- `Button/LG`, `LargeButton` → `Button size="lg"`

### Form Elements
- `Input`, `TextField`, `TextInput` → `Input`
- `Textarea`, `TextArea` → `Textarea`
- `Checkbox` → `Checkbox`
- `Switch`, `Toggle` → `Switch`
- `RadioGroup`, `RadioButtons` → `RadioGroup`
- `Select`, `Dropdown` → `Select`
- `Label`, `FieldLabel` → `Label`

### Containers
- `Card` → `Card`
- `Card/Header` → `CardHeader`
- `Card/Content`, `Card/Body` → `CardContent`
- `Card/Footer` → `CardFooter`

### Overlays
- `Dialog`, `Modal` → `Dialog`
- `Sheet`, `Drawer`, `SlideOut` → `Sheet`
- `Popover` → `Popover`
- `Tooltip` → `Tooltip`
- `AlertDialog`, `ConfirmDialog` → `AlertDialog`

### Navigation
- `Tabs` → `Tabs`
- `TabsList`, `TabBar` → `TabsList`
- `Tab`, `TabItem` → `TabsTrigger`
- `TabPanel`, `TabContent` → `TabsContent`
- `DropdownMenu`, `Menu` → `DropdownMenu`
- `MenuItem` → `DropdownMenuItem`

### Data Display
- `Table` → `Table`
- `TableHeader`, `TableHead` → `TableHeader`
- `TableRow`, `Row` → `TableRow`
- `TableCell`, `Cell` → `TableCell`
- `Badge`, `Tag`, `Chip` → `Badge`
- `Avatar` → `Avatar`
- `Separator`, `Divider`, `HR` → `Separator`
- `Skeleton`, `Placeholder` → `Skeleton`

### Feedback
- `Alert`, `Banner` → `Alert`
- `Toast`, `Notification` → Sonner toast()
- `Progress`, `ProgressBar` → `Progress`

---

## Breakpoint Guidelines

Match Figma frames to Tailwind breakpoints:

| Figma Frame Width | Tailwind Prefix | Description |
|-------------------|-----------------|-------------|
| < 640px | (default) | Mobile |
| 640px+ | `sm:` | Small tablets |
| 768px+ | `md:` | Tablets |
| 1024px+ | `lg:` | Small laptops |
| 1280px+ | `xl:` | Desktops |
| 1536px+ | `2xl:` | Large screens |

---

## Quality Checklist

Before submitting code:

- [ ] All interactive elements use shadcn components
- [ ] No raw `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>` elements
- [ ] Layout matches Figma spacing exactly
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints implemented
- [ ] Dark mode supported (if applicable)
- [ ] All styles are Tailwind classes
- [ ] Component mapping was approved before coding

